{"questionId":"1fc2cc40-1a64-44a1-8ebe-eca45e868415_19","correctAnswer":"D","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"To find the $y$-intercept of $y = 6^x + 12$, set $x = 0$."},{"title":"Solve","content":"$y = 6^0 + 12 = 1 + 12 = 13$"},{"title":"Answer","content":"The $y$-intercept is $(0, 13)$. <strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}